This paper focuses on optimizing energy harvesting for multiuser multicarrier mobile wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses power allocation and optimization, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes frameworks for joint data and energy transfer, which can be considered as a control systems problem (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of multimedia applications (cs.MM) and mathematical optimization techniques (cs.MA) in their evaluation studies.
